> Punchy and smoky with a spicy kick, Cajun spice mix contains ingredients such as chilli powder, ground cumin, oregano and thyme. The spiced Cajun sauce pairs perfectly with the creamy filling of the ricotta pasta.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{240%ml} to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the ravioli.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim the @courgette{1}, then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into 1cm chunks.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

When hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and courgette and cook, ~{8-10%mins} total. Turn only every couple of mins. Once cooked, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then transfer both to a #bowl{}. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @spinach and ricotta ravioli{250%g} to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{3%mins}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}.

Drizzle with @oil{} and gently stir through to stop it sticking together.

Wipe out the (now empty) pan and pop on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Stir in the garlic and @Cajun spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), cook for ~{1%min}.

Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, @creme fraiche{75%g}, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and water for the sauce to the pan.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%mins}.

Once the sauce has thickened, remove from the heat. Stir in the @butter{20%g} and the @hard Italian style cheese{20%g}(grated) until melted.

Gently stir the cooked ravioli, chicken and charred courgette into the sauce. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of water if needed.

Share the creamy Cajun ravioli between your #bowls{}.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g}. Drizzle with the @balsamic glaze{12%ml} to finish.

Enjoy!